<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="RAG Retrieval">
  <data key="d0">RAG Retrieval</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">RAG Retrieval is a retrieval process that runs concurrently with intent classification, but is cancelled if the intent is conversational.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846942</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Retrieval Latency">
  <data key="d0">Retrieval Latency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Retrieval Latency refers to the delay before the first token of the LLM response is streamed, which is minimized by points 1-3 of the implementation notes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846942</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intent Classification">
  <data key="d0">Intent Classification</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Intent Classification is a process run concurrently with RAG retrieval to save time when identifying user intents in interactions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846945</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LLM Model">
  <data key="d0">LLM Model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">LLM Model is part of the chat system used for language processing tasks, with its concurrency limit for async jobs recently increased to improve performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846946</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LightRAG">
  <data key="d0">LightRAG</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">LightRAG is a query mode for entity-focused vector/graph retrieval, designed to be fast and accurate for point-lookup questions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846947</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Asyncio">
  <data key="d0">Asyncio</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Asyncio is a Python library used to run asynchronous tasks, such as running intent classification and RAG retrieval concurrently.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846947</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Qdrant">
  <data key="d0">Qdrant</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Qdrant holds retrieval results, and its top_k parameter can be tuned to balance between speed and accuracy in queries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846947</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Classification">
  <data key="d0">Classification</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Classification is a heuristic short-circuit used for intents, particularly for short follow-up queries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846948</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Health-Check Warm-Up">
  <data key="d0">Health-Check Warm-Up</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Health-Check Warm-Up involves pre-initializing systems to prevent delays in processing the first request.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846948</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Streaming">
  <data key="d0">Streaming</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Streaming involves sending tokens to the browser as they arrive from the LLM, affecting perceived latency of responses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846949</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="FastAPI">
  <data key="d0">FastAPI</data>
  <data key="d1">framework</data>
  <data key="d2">FastAPI is the web framework used for managing server-side operations and processes, including request handling strategies like Health-Check Warm-Up.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846956</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="UptimeRobot">
  <data key="d0">UptimeRobot</data>
  <data key="d1">tool</data>
  <data key="d2">UptimeRobot is a tool used to keep services active by sending periodic pings, aiding in maintenance of system readiness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846956</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Railway Free Tier">
  <data key="d0">Railway Free Tier</data>
  <data key="d1">service</data>
  <data key="d2">Railway Free Tier is a hosting service that may experience added latency after idle periods, affecting response time.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846956</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Render">
  <data key="d0">Render</data>
  <data key="d1">service</data>
  <data key="d2">Render is a hosting service, with settings options like minimum instances to prevent sleep mode and maintain service readiness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846957</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chat Process">
  <data key="d0">Chat Process</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Chat Process involves concurrent operations like history fetch and message persistence, which determines connection pool sizing based on latency data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846957</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Asyncio.create_task">
  <data key="d0">Asyncio.create_task</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Asyncio.create_task is a method used within the context of the Asyncio library to execute asynchronous tasks in parallel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b4aa97eb500d161464a14c94ae6047c2</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846957</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="History Fetch">
  <data key="d0">History Fetch</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">History Fetch refers to the method of maintaining a connection to retrieve historical data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846959</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Message Persist">
  <data key="d0">Message Persist</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Message Persist refers to the method of maintaining a connection to ensure messages are stored.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846960</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="P95 Latency">
  <data key="d0">P95 Latency</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">P95 Latency is a metric that measures latency at the 95th percentile under load.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846965</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pool Timeout">
  <data key="d0">Pool Timeout</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pool Timeout is a configuration parameter that generates errors reported in logs, used as a signal for monitoring load stress.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846965</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pool Size">
  <data key="d0">Pool Size</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pool Size is a configuration parameter that can be increased to improve performance, suggested up to a size of 10.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846965</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Response Streaming">
  <data key="d0">Response Streaming</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Response Streaming is a method of transmitting tokens to the browser as they are received from the LLM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846966</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Perceived Latency">
  <data key="d0">Perceived Latency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Perceived Latency refers to the time perceived by users, notably measured by the time-to-first-token.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846967</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LLM">
  <data key="d0">LLM</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">LLM refers to the language model producing tokens during response streaming.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846967</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Time-To-First-Token">
  <data key="d0">Time-To-First-Token</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Time-To-First-Token (TTFT) is a metric that gauges latency from the intent stage through retrieval to the first token output.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846969</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tokens">
  <data key="d0">Tokens</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dcd6b1fd8f26bb84cb9d480ce1372752</data>
  <data key="d2">Tokens are transmitted to the browser using the Response Streaming method as they are produced by the LLM.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">d3ff01e3-398a-4879-916a-a7085be7b28d</data>
  <data key="d5">1773846983</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
